verbose_text: In a more recent study, they determined HER2 levels by IHC in two cohorts of 10 and 19 breast cancer samples, but a correlation between IHC and SRM data was observed only in the first cohort, suggesting to the authors that many patients with a 3+ IHC staining for HER2 probably do not express elevated levels of this protein and are therefore unlikely to benefit from trastuzumab XREF_BIBR.
